			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This spell is awesome.  I still swear by it after using it for 13 levels.  Soloing yellows and low reds with this pattern:  Eng Darkness, send pet in, Fear, Heart Flutter, Heat Blood, Infectious Cloud, Re-Fear if needed, then lifetap if needed. In my experience, the eng darkness slows the mob down noticeably and Fear makes them slowly run away while the pet whacks em.  Also, the mob will often try to run but the stacked Dots and damage from the skelly slows em down to a crawl.  If they are slowly running and down to their last bit of health I call off the pet and sit and med.  I love watching em just fall over without being wacked and my pet comes back with over 50% of his hps left.  This spell does get resisted now and again but your pet can buy you time to cast it again.  I can't wait for the upgrade at 34.  Here's to the dark side.
				</font>
			</td>

